    <h2>
        Welcome FPT-Aptech</h2>
    <div class="quote">
        <p align="justify">
            On May 25<sup>th</sup>, FPT Technology Research Institute was officially launched
            at FPT University. Officially receiving the establishment decision on 1 April, 2010
            , FPT Technology Research Institute is 100% financed by FPT Corporation and directly
            managed by FPT University. It is expected that, in 2010, FPT Corporation will invest
            VND 3.5 billion in the operation of the Institute.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="content">
        <p align="justify">
            Accordingly, the Institute will focus on four directions: information technology
            application, clean energy and energy saving; biotechnology and space technology.
        </p>
        <p align="justify">
            <i>&quot;The establishment of this Institute marks a significant step over 20 years
                of the Group’s development. Lately established but with the combination of enterprises,
                schools, science and technology, FPT Technology Research Institute will be the interference
                and convergence of all factors to be come a place to research on application of
                advanced development of science and technology, serving for the development of domestic
                industries. FPT Technology Research Institute has desire to quickly bring new technologies
                to effectively apply for Vietnam in general and&nbsp; for FPT in particular.&quot;
            </i>said Dr. Tran The Trung, the director of the FPT Technology Research Institute.<em>&nbsp;</em></p>
        <p align="justify">
            Besides, the establishment of FPT Technology Research Institute also create s a
            good environment to attract and gather a lot of &quot;talents&quot; not only in
            Vietnam but also in the world to research and develop industries and make contribution
            to the development of the nation’s economy.
        </p>
        <p align="justify">
            For that purpose, the main function s of the Institute are to research and develop
            technology and science and training. The Institute will conduct science and technology
            research activities under agreements not only with FPT Corporation but also with
            domestic or overseas individuals and organizations. Besides that, the Institute
            also aims at building training programs and performing transfers of knowledge, information,
            technology and products.
        </p>
        <p align="justify">
            At the opening ceremony, FPT Technology Research Institute signed cooperation agreements
            with five research agencies, including the Institute of Information Technology under
            the Hanoi National University, The Vietnam Foudation, FPT Software, Asia Petro and
            FBM Biology and Regenerated Medicine Joint Stock Company in the areas of information
            technology, using and develo ment of opened Education Resources programs, initiating
            technology ideas, supporting the development of the Association of the Vietnam regenerated
            energy and fuel, research and apply the stem cell technology in health and beauty
            care.
        </p>
        <p align="justify">
            Currently, the Institute has been conducting 10 research and development projects,
            two of which have been implemented, including the Fspace satellite and picture processing
            projects. With the satellite project, the FPT Technology Research Institute targets
            to complete a satellite this year. If it is a success, this will be the first private
            satellite to be launch into space in Vietnam. Further targets of the Institute are
            to commercialize and develop Fspace to be a company and by 2011, the Institute will
            have at least one patent.
        </p>
    </div>
